interfaces

Interface IntersectionFinder<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the data type of elements in the sets. It is assumed that it is always instantiated to an object data type that has overridden its own version of the equals method from the Object class.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractIntersectionFinder, P1P2, P3, P4

    public interface IntersectionFinder<E>
    An object of this type is capable of finding the intersection of a family of sets of elements of a particular data type.
